def _get_grouper(
    obj,
    key=None,
    axis=0,
    level=None,
    sort=True,
    observed=False,
    mutated=False,
    validate=True,
):
    group_axis = obj._get_axis(axis)

    # Handling of the key parameter
    if key is None:
        key = group_axis
    elif isinstance(key, Grouper):
        binner, grouper, obj = key._get_grouper(obj, validate=False)
        if key.key is None:
            return grouper, [], obj
        else:
            return grouper, {key.key}, obj
    elif isinstance(key, BaseGrouper):
        return key, [], obj
    elif isinstance(key, (str, list)):
        key = [key] if isinstance(key, str) else key
    else:
        raise ValueError("Invalid key parameter")

    # Additional code logic to create the groupings and exclusions
    groupings = [
        Grouping(
            group_axis,
            obj[key],
            name=key,
            level=level,
            sort=sort,
            observed=observed,
            in_axis=True,
        )
    for key in keys]

    exclusions = [col for col in obj.columns if col not in keys]

    # create the internals grouper
    grouper = BaseGrouper(
        group_axis,
        groupings,
        sort=sort,
        mutated=mutated
    )

    return grouper, exclusions, obj
